1
00:00:26,297 --> 00:00:27,423
Ms. Kiryu.

2
00:00:27,507 --> 00:00:28,466
Please sign this.

3
00:00:28,550 --> 00:00:29,551
Okay.

4
00:00:37,684 --> 00:00:39,686
You look like you don't get it at all.

5
00:00:39,769 --> 00:00:41,563
-No, I'll check it.
-Thank you.

6
00:00:41,646 --> 00:00:43,857
This too, please.
April's post-mortem reports.

7
00:00:43,940 --> 00:00:45,859
And here is the summary
of the test results.

8
00:00:46,442 --> 00:00:47,277
Got it.

9
00:00:47,360 --> 00:00:48,945
-Thank you.
-Thank you.

10
00:00:49,529 --> 00:00:51,281
Will you really be okay?

11
00:00:51,364 --> 00:00:52,991
Yes, it's no problem at all.

12
00:00:53,074 --> 00:00:54,033
Of course it isn't.

13
00:00:54,117 --> 00:00:56,619
Ms. Kiryu is the head of MEJ, after all.

14
00:00:56,703 --> 00:00:57,662
Right?

15
00:00:57,745 --> 00:00:58,746
Yes.

16
00:01:01,833 --> 00:01:03,793
Here is the summary
of the chemical analysis.

17
00:01:03,877 --> 00:01:05,170
Please sign it.

18
00:01:10,925 --> 00:01:12,635
I'm going to step out for a bit.

19
00:01:12,719 --> 00:01:15,180
My boss at the Ministry of Health
is calling for me.

20
00:01:16,639 --> 00:01:18,349
-She ran away.
-She certainly did.

21
00:01:22,854 --> 00:01:26,566
Regarding that youth poverty support
project you were moving forward with,

22
00:01:26,649 --> 00:01:28,192
it is finally ready to launch.

23
00:01:28,276 --> 00:01:29,402
What?

24
00:01:29,485 --> 00:01:30,528
Really?

25
00:01:30,612 --> 00:01:33,781
However, since you are busy
with the MEJ now,

26
00:01:33,865 --> 00:01:36,743
I have decided to put
another person in charge of it.

27
00:01:36,826 --> 00:01:37,660
What?

28
00:01:37,744 --> 00:01:39,454
Keep up the good work over there.

29
00:01:57,889 --> 00:01:58,932
Is something wrong?

30
00:01:59,015 --> 00:01:59,974
Well…

31
00:02:00,058 --> 00:02:02,936
It seems your hands have stopped moving.

32
00:02:03,811 --> 00:02:05,813
Oh, yes, they have.

33
00:02:06,689 --> 00:02:10,401
I'm just stamping seals. I'll be fine.
I'll finish it after this all-nighter.

34
00:02:10,485 --> 00:02:12,153
I wouldn't recommend that.

35
00:02:12,237 --> 00:02:14,614
Staying up all night
is the same as being drunk.

36
00:02:15,490 --> 00:02:16,324
Drunk?

37
00:02:16,407 --> 00:02:19,077
Cognitive function
after 24 hours without sleep

38
00:02:19,160 --> 00:02:22,705
is reportedly at the same level
as a blood alcohol concentration

39
00:02:22,789 --> 00:02:24,207
of 0.10 percent.

40
00:02:24,290 --> 00:02:27,627
Information cannot be retained
by the brain in that state.

41
00:02:27,710 --> 00:02:29,671
But I won't finish unless I work
all night.

42
00:02:29,754 --> 00:02:33,299
That said, research shows that women
who sleep for less than four hours

43
00:02:33,383 --> 00:02:36,678
have twice the mortality risk
compared to sleeping seven hours.

44
00:02:36,761 --> 00:02:40,014
By pulling an all-nighter,
you think you're increasing your time,

45
00:02:40,098 --> 00:02:43,851
but you might actually be decreasing it.

46
00:02:45,853 --> 00:02:47,397
I will be careful.

47
00:02:47,480 --> 00:02:48,564
As much as I can.

48
00:02:48,648 --> 00:02:49,482
Okay then!

49
00:02:54,320 --> 00:02:55,321
Hello.

50
00:02:55,405 --> 00:02:56,489
Good evening.

51
00:02:56,572 --> 00:02:58,324
It happened in the owner's room.

52
00:02:58,408 --> 00:02:59,575
This way.

53
00:03:02,704 --> 00:03:04,956
The victim is 39-year-old Hayato Kuriyama.

54
00:03:05,039 --> 00:03:06,416
The owner of this club.

55
00:03:06,499 --> 00:03:10,378
A host from a partner club found the body
when he came for a meeting.

56
00:03:17,927 --> 00:03:21,514
Fine white froth is visible
around the nose and mouth.

57
00:03:21,597 --> 00:03:23,725
There is a possibility of drowning.

58
00:03:23,808 --> 00:03:24,642
Drowning?

59
00:03:24,726 --> 00:03:27,478
You mean he drowned inside a closet?

60
00:03:27,562 --> 00:03:30,815
It would be difficult to kill him outside
and move him here.

61
00:03:30,898 --> 00:03:33,359
But drowning inside a room?

62
00:03:33,443 --> 00:03:36,863
It is possible as long as there is enough
water to cover the mouth and nose.

63
00:03:45,455 --> 00:03:48,916
The autopsy shows
that the cause of death was drowning.

64
00:03:49,000 --> 00:03:50,251
Components of the cleaning agent

65
00:03:50,335 --> 00:03:53,087
used in the room's toilet were
detected in the water inside the lungs.

66
00:03:53,171 --> 00:03:57,342
We found pressure marks on the neck
and a slight bruise on the head.

67
00:03:57,425 --> 00:03:59,052
Both occurred while he was alive.

68
00:03:59,135 --> 00:04:01,012
We also found skin fragments

69
00:04:01,095 --> 00:04:03,264
under his fingernails
that don't belong to Mr. Kuriyama.

70
00:04:03,348 --> 00:04:04,557
Testing revealed

71
00:04:05,099 --> 00:04:07,643
that it is female DNA.

72
00:04:09,562 --> 00:04:11,022
Female…

73
00:04:11,105 --> 00:04:14,400
Did the victim
have any trouble with women?

74
00:04:14,484 --> 00:04:17,695
When he took a liking to a girl,
he would try to keep her for himself.

75
00:04:17,779 --> 00:04:19,405
They were too scared to refuse.

76
00:04:19,489 --> 00:04:21,574
Some girls were backed into a corner.

77
00:04:21,657 --> 00:04:24,452
Had he been clashing
with anyone in particular lately?

78
00:04:30,124 --> 00:04:31,334
Well, actually,

79
00:04:32,335 --> 00:04:35,171
<i>one girl was arguing with him</i>
<i>about breaking up.</i>

80
00:04:41,886 --> 00:04:43,096
Excuse me.

81
00:04:44,430 --> 00:04:45,515
Police.

82
00:04:48,643 --> 00:04:49,811
Police?

83
00:04:49,894 --> 00:04:53,231
Could you come with us to the station
to discuss Hayato Kuriyama?

84
00:04:53,314 --> 00:04:54,899
I'm sorry.

85
00:04:54,982 --> 00:04:57,527
I have to go to work now.

86
00:04:58,194 --> 00:05:01,739
Female DNA was detected on the body.

87
00:05:11,916 --> 00:05:15,920
Will you cooperate with a DNA test?

88
00:05:22,093 --> 00:05:23,553
I'm sorry.

89
00:05:27,432 --> 00:05:29,225
I'm sorry.

90
00:05:32,103 --> 00:05:33,563
<i>The culprit is 24-year-old</i>

91
00:05:33,646 --> 00:05:35,731
Miyuki Yanagihara,
an employee at the club.

92
00:05:35,815 --> 00:05:39,652
She visited the victim's room
on the day of the crime.

93
00:05:40,236 --> 00:05:42,113
Please just let me go.

94
00:05:45,283 --> 00:05:46,909
I'm at my limit.

95
00:05:56,210 --> 00:05:57,670
I'll kill you if you run away.

96
00:06:27,241 --> 00:06:29,869
<i>She put poison in his protein shake</i>
<i>and left the room.</i>

97
00:06:30,786 --> 00:06:31,746
<i>However…</i>

98
00:06:31,829 --> 00:06:33,247
Where's your earring?

99
00:06:33,331 --> 00:06:34,165
What?

100
00:06:37,877 --> 00:06:38,794
One second.

101
00:07:28,594 --> 00:07:31,973
So then, she strangled the victim
after he regained consciousness.

102
00:07:36,644 --> 00:07:39,855
<i>After that,</i>
<i>fearing he would wake up again,</i>

103
00:07:39,939 --> 00:07:41,941
<i>she submerged his face in the toilet.</i>

104
00:07:48,739 --> 00:07:49,824
What?

105
00:07:49,907 --> 00:07:52,994
But no poison was detected
in the autopsy, was it?

106
00:07:53,077 --> 00:07:55,997
The components checked
in the initial screening are limited.

107
00:07:56,080 --> 00:08:00,626
Irregular toxins won't be detected
unless we specifically test for them.

108
00:08:00,710 --> 00:08:01,544
Test for them?

109
00:08:01,627 --> 00:08:04,171
What was the substance used?

110
00:08:04,797 --> 00:08:08,342
She's actually remaining silent
about the poison.

111
00:08:09,010 --> 00:08:10,219
<i>What poison was it?</i>

112
00:08:11,470 --> 00:08:13,180
Where did you get it?

113
00:08:16,642 --> 00:08:18,185
I forgot.

114
00:08:18,269 --> 00:08:19,312
What?

115
00:08:19,395 --> 00:08:20,479
Why?

116
00:08:21,272 --> 00:08:23,024
Maybe she's protecting someone.

117
00:08:23,107 --> 00:08:26,360
In that case, finding the toxin
could be quite difficult.

118
00:08:26,444 --> 00:08:29,739
For now, let's broaden
the scope of the analysis.

119
00:08:29,822 --> 00:08:30,948
-Okay.
-Okay.

120
00:08:31,032 --> 00:08:33,784
We will investigate
the source of procurement as well.

121
00:08:36,370 --> 00:08:37,204
Hello?

122
00:08:39,081 --> 00:08:40,708
Huh? What do you mean?

123
00:08:43,711 --> 00:08:44,754
I'll be right back.

124
00:08:46,881 --> 00:08:47,923
What happened?

125
00:08:49,216 --> 00:08:51,636
A staff member from the club
turned himself in.

126
00:08:54,305 --> 00:08:57,224
He says he was the one
who killed the owner.

127
00:09:04,815 --> 00:09:06,776
I'm the one who did it.

128
00:09:07,360 --> 00:09:10,196
That day, I went
to talk to him about a loan.

129
00:09:10,696 --> 00:09:11,906
Please, I beg you!

130
00:09:12,531 --> 00:09:14,116
Are you stupid?

131
00:09:20,748 --> 00:09:21,916
Bastard!

132
00:09:35,513 --> 00:09:38,015
<i>After that, I got scared</i>

133
00:09:38,099 --> 00:09:39,517
and ran away.

134
00:09:40,142 --> 00:09:44,230
But then I saw on the news
that Miyuki had been arrested.

135
00:09:44,980 --> 00:09:46,440
It was all my fault.

136
00:09:47,566 --> 00:09:49,485
Miyuki is innocent.

137
00:09:49,568 --> 00:09:51,362
Please, arrest me now!

138
00:09:51,445 --> 00:09:52,488
Mr. Murano.

139
00:09:53,572 --> 00:09:56,951
Did you really kill him by strangulation?

140
00:09:57,743 --> 00:09:58,703
Yes.

141
00:10:02,248 --> 00:10:04,709
She has already admitted to the crime.

142
00:10:04,792 --> 00:10:07,294
That's impossible! Please, investigate!

143
00:10:07,378 --> 00:10:08,379
Like I said…

144
00:10:08,462 --> 00:10:10,339
Where is the ashtray you used to hit him?

145
00:10:10,423 --> 00:10:11,465
Hey.

146
00:10:12,174 --> 00:10:13,718
I threw it into the Ooguri River.

147
00:10:17,596 --> 00:10:19,682
Why did you ask about the murder weapon?

148
00:10:19,765 --> 00:10:22,351
The bruise on the top of the victim's head

149
00:10:22,435 --> 00:10:25,730
might have been caused
by Murano hitting him.

150
00:10:25,813 --> 00:10:29,191
If we find the weapon and match it,
we can be certain.

151
00:10:29,275 --> 00:10:33,946
Wasn't that just from bumping into
something when dragging him around?

152
00:10:34,029 --> 00:10:36,407
Besides, the cause of death
was drowning, right?

153
00:10:36,490 --> 00:10:40,703
Murano's statement
that he strangled him doesn't add up.

154
00:10:40,786 --> 00:10:43,914
It's only natural to consider
Miyuki Yanagihara as the culprit.

155
00:10:43,998 --> 00:10:48,043
Murano is just giving a false confession
to protect Miyuki Yanagihara.

156
00:10:48,127 --> 00:10:49,545
Miyuki is innocent.

157
00:10:49,628 --> 00:10:51,255
Please, arrest me now!

158
00:10:51,338 --> 00:10:54,258
However, as long as
no poison has been detected,

159
00:10:54,341 --> 00:10:57,219
we should investigate
assuming every possibility.

160
00:10:57,303 --> 00:11:00,765
Let's investigate their relationship and
search for the murder weapon.

161
00:11:00,848 --> 00:11:02,767
-Supervisor.
-Yes?

162
00:11:02,850 --> 00:11:05,603
The cause of death
has been determined to be drowning.

163
00:11:05,686 --> 00:11:08,981
There's no need for the MEJ
to investigate any further, is there?

164
00:11:09,940 --> 00:11:11,776
Oh, well…

165
00:11:12,902 --> 00:11:15,988
The MEJ has the authority to conduct
all general investigations to--

166
00:11:16,071 --> 00:11:18,365
Do you have anything else
besides "authority"?

167
00:11:19,116 --> 00:11:21,535
How can you call yourself the supervisor?

168
00:11:23,162 --> 00:11:24,121
Let's go.

169
00:11:24,205 --> 00:11:25,039
Yes, ma'am!

170
00:11:28,626 --> 00:11:31,462
We have no choice but to move on our own.

171
00:11:32,546 --> 00:11:36,383
Could you investigate the relationship
between Yanagihara and Murano?

172
00:11:36,967 --> 00:11:38,844
What? Me?

173
00:11:38,928 --> 00:11:41,597
I will proceed
with identifying the poison.

174
00:11:41,680 --> 00:11:43,349
I'm counting on you.

175
00:11:53,275 --> 00:11:54,985
Are we looking for it after all?

176
00:11:55,069 --> 00:11:58,322
We were told the weapon was thrown away,
so we have no choice.

177
00:11:59,573 --> 00:12:01,492
Here I thought I could go home today.

178
00:12:01,575 --> 00:12:03,452
I wanted to finish early too.

179
00:12:03,536 --> 00:12:04,954
Do you have any plans?

180
00:12:05,037 --> 00:12:06,288
I do.

181
00:12:06,372 --> 00:12:07,498
I'm getting snacks,

182
00:12:07,581 --> 00:12:10,584
watch a reality-TV show
while drinking wine, and doze off.

183
00:12:10,668 --> 00:12:12,795
Wait. Ms. Dojima, you watch dating shows?

184
00:12:13,379 --> 00:12:14,296
I do.

185
00:12:14,380 --> 00:12:18,092
Wow, you're actually interested in love
and things like that?

186
00:12:20,177 --> 00:12:23,681
Even I have interests in things
that aren't violent and terrible.

187
00:12:39,280 --> 00:12:40,281
We're taking a break!

188
00:12:40,364 --> 00:12:41,824
We're taking a break.

189
00:12:49,832 --> 00:12:52,293
I mean, how long are we going to do this?

190
00:12:54,253 --> 00:12:56,797
The culprit is Miyuki Yanagihara.

191
00:12:56,880 --> 00:12:59,258
We're not going to find that ash tray!

192
00:13:01,719 --> 00:13:04,471
Something's bothering me.

193
00:13:05,139 --> 00:13:08,559
Nothing came up in the gas chromatography
or liquid chromatography.

194
00:13:09,059 --> 00:13:11,437
Capillary chromatography is also negative.

195
00:13:12,479 --> 00:13:13,647
Damn it!

196
00:13:14,356 --> 00:13:17,151
We'd have no trouble
if she just said what it was.

197
00:13:17,234 --> 00:13:18,944
I wonder why she won't.

198
00:13:19,028 --> 00:13:21,655
Maybe that club staff member
got it for her.

199
00:13:22,615 --> 00:13:25,909
I think she's staying silent
to protect him.

200
00:13:25,993 --> 00:13:28,704
So they're both covering for each other?

201
00:13:28,787 --> 00:13:29,580
Exactly.

202
00:13:29,663 --> 00:13:33,751
Is there a possibility that there was
no poison in the first place?

203
00:13:33,834 --> 00:13:36,503
Kuriyama had pulmonary edema.

204
00:13:36,587 --> 00:13:41,300
While it's a finding seen in drowning,
it can also occur in drug poisoning.

205
00:13:41,925 --> 00:13:46,096
We cannot deny the possibility that
some kind of drug was ingested.

206
00:13:47,264 --> 00:13:49,099
I'm asking again.

207
00:13:49,767 --> 00:13:52,394
How did you get the poison?

208
00:13:54,980 --> 00:13:56,899
Why won't you tell me?

209
00:14:01,779 --> 00:14:04,531
You're protecting someone, aren't you?

210
00:14:06,075 --> 00:14:07,034
A lover…

211
00:14:08,577 --> 00:14:09,495
perhaps?

212
00:14:15,668 --> 00:14:20,589
Were Miyuki and Murano possibly
dating in secret, without telling anyone?

213
00:14:20,673 --> 00:14:22,967
No, I can't imagine they were.

214
00:14:23,926 --> 00:14:25,636
The owner would have them killed.

215
00:14:27,513 --> 00:14:30,349
When did Miyuki start working at the club?

216
00:14:30,933 --> 00:14:32,559
About a year ago, I think.

217
00:14:32,643 --> 00:14:35,062
She had money problems
and was looking for a new job.

218
00:14:35,145 --> 00:14:38,023
What kind of person was Murano?

219
00:14:38,107 --> 00:14:39,692
He was actually a former host.

220
00:14:39,775 --> 00:14:43,445
He was working at an affiliate club
and moved here.

221
00:14:43,529 --> 00:14:45,823
Do you know the name of that host club?

222
00:14:49,368 --> 00:14:50,786
Supervisor!

223
00:14:51,495 --> 00:14:52,413
Why are you here?

224
00:14:53,706 --> 00:14:56,000
To interview involved parties.

225
00:14:56,083 --> 00:14:57,543
Without telling the police?

226
00:14:57,626 --> 00:14:58,961
It was Dr. Masumi's instruction.

227
00:14:59,044 --> 00:15:01,422
You just do whatever
people tell you, don't you?

228
00:15:01,505 --> 00:15:02,589
Excuse me.

229
00:15:07,428 --> 00:15:08,721
A host club?

230
00:15:09,680 --> 00:15:11,515
So that's your hobby?

231
00:15:12,266 --> 00:15:15,102
No! It's Murano's former workplace.

232
00:15:15,769 --> 00:15:17,771
I thought I might learn something.

233
00:15:22,943 --> 00:15:24,570
Are you coming?

234
00:15:24,653 --> 00:15:25,487
What?

235
00:15:26,280 --> 00:15:29,450
You'll just move around secretly
on your own anyway, right?

236
00:15:32,619 --> 00:15:35,497
Murano was a good guy.
He wasn't suited to being a host.

237
00:15:35,581 --> 00:15:38,625
Had you heard anything from Murano?

238
00:15:38,709 --> 00:15:41,170
About trouble with the owner,

239
00:15:41,253 --> 00:15:44,506
or about a hostess
named Miyuki Yanagihara?

240
00:15:46,258 --> 00:15:48,510
I'm not sure.

241
00:15:52,056 --> 00:15:53,140
It's 100,000?

242
00:15:53,223 --> 00:15:55,726
-One of those then.
-What?

243
00:15:55,809 --> 00:15:58,187
Champagne coming up!

244
00:15:58,270 --> 00:16:00,355
Thank you, welcome to the club!

245
00:16:00,439 --> 00:16:02,149
-Welcome!
-Welcome!

246
00:16:02,232 --> 00:16:03,358
All right!

247
00:16:03,942 --> 00:16:05,152
Thanks.

248
00:16:06,820 --> 00:16:08,697
What? Aren't the police
supposed to pay this?

249
00:16:08,781 --> 00:16:11,950
You're the supervisor, right?
Figure it out with your budget.

250
00:16:13,619 --> 00:16:16,872
Want to go get food?
I'll at least make that my treat.

251
00:16:18,415 --> 00:16:19,750
Let's go.

252
00:16:25,380 --> 00:16:27,466
NO DRUGS TARGETED FOR SCREENING DETECTED

253
00:16:35,224 --> 00:16:38,268
Getting a hostess job
because of financial trouble, huh?

254
00:16:38,352 --> 00:16:42,314
Many young people can't earn enough
even if they work full-time

255
00:16:42,397 --> 00:16:45,150
due to non-regular employment
and low wages.

256
00:16:45,234 --> 00:16:47,736
So they end up in the nightlife business.

257
00:16:47,820 --> 00:16:49,613
You're surprisingly well-informed.

258
00:16:49,696 --> 00:16:52,032
Originally, I wanted to
work in social welfare

259
00:16:52,116 --> 00:16:54,576
because I wanted to help those people.

260
00:16:54,660 --> 00:16:56,203
Before coming to MEJ,

261
00:16:56,286 --> 00:16:58,914
I was in youth poverty support
for a long time.

262
00:16:59,665 --> 00:17:03,001
Why is someone as noble as you
the MEJ supervisor?

263
00:17:03,085 --> 00:17:06,463
Poverty support and
the cause of death are totally different.

264
00:17:13,095 --> 00:17:14,471
You got transferred.

265
00:17:16,890 --> 00:17:17,724
Yes.

266
00:17:21,562 --> 00:17:25,315
Of course, I intend to work
as hard as I can in any way I can.

267
00:17:26,733 --> 00:17:27,943
But, to be honest,

268
00:17:28,819 --> 00:17:31,155
I still want to return to the MHLW.

269
00:17:35,742 --> 00:17:37,327
That might be perfect, actually.

270
00:17:37,870 --> 00:17:38,787
What?

271
00:17:39,580 --> 00:17:43,250
If you've done that kind of work,
don't you understand how she feels?

272
00:17:44,084 --> 00:17:44,960
You know,

273
00:17:45,586 --> 00:17:47,963
she has stopped talking to the police.

274
00:17:49,673 --> 00:17:51,508
Why don't you try talking to her?

275
00:17:57,764 --> 00:17:59,808
My name is Kiryu from MEJ.

276
00:18:01,977 --> 00:18:03,645
We're an MHLW organization

277
00:18:03,729 --> 00:18:06,106
that specializes in determining
causes of death.

278
00:18:07,941 --> 00:18:09,860
No matter how many times you ask,

279
00:18:10,944 --> 00:18:12,946
I don't remember anything
about the poison.

280
00:18:19,828 --> 00:18:21,330
Are you protecting Murano?

281
00:18:23,665 --> 00:18:24,875
Murano?

282
00:18:26,627 --> 00:18:29,296
What has he got to do with it?

283
00:18:30,797 --> 00:18:31,882
Actually,

284
00:18:33,300 --> 00:18:35,219
Murano turned himself in.

285
00:18:39,139 --> 00:18:40,057
What?

286
00:18:48,357 --> 00:18:52,569
What was your relationship with Murano?

287
00:18:54,655 --> 00:18:55,906
Murano…

288
00:18:57,783 --> 00:19:00,077
was always supporting me.

289
00:19:04,206 --> 00:19:07,459
I started this job
to pay back my student loans.

290
00:19:08,710 --> 00:19:10,420
I've always regretted it.

291
00:19:12,089 --> 00:19:13,298
Student loans?

292
00:19:14,091 --> 00:19:16,218
My family was poor.

293
00:19:16,885 --> 00:19:19,346
I went to a beautician school
on a scholarship.

294
00:19:22,266 --> 00:19:25,102
But the salary
for an assistant was low, so…

295
00:19:28,021 --> 00:19:30,357
I started a part-time job
at a hostess club.

296
00:19:31,108 --> 00:19:32,859
You don't have to worry anymore.

297
00:19:34,403 --> 00:19:37,239
Some girls work only until
they've paid back their scholarships.

298
00:19:39,783 --> 00:19:41,326
Thank you very much.

299
00:19:42,494 --> 00:19:43,704
<i>But in the end,</i>

300
00:19:44,496 --> 00:19:46,248
I was forced to become his mistress.

301
00:19:49,501 --> 00:19:50,961
Before I knew it…

302
00:19:53,046 --> 00:19:54,798
I had nowhere else to go

303
00:19:55,716 --> 00:19:57,634
and no place to return to.

304
00:19:59,094 --> 00:20:02,222
<i>I had no choice</i>
<i>but to rely on that man to live.</i>

305
00:20:05,517 --> 00:20:06,810
And during that time…

306
00:20:07,436 --> 00:20:09,271
I'm here for you.

307
00:20:10,605 --> 00:20:13,233
<i>…Murano encouraged me.</i>

308
00:20:14,192 --> 00:20:16,695
I had to do my best to get out of there…

309
00:20:19,239 --> 00:20:21,700
and started to believe that I could.

310
00:20:23,744 --> 00:20:24,745
But…

311
00:20:30,792 --> 00:20:33,045
How did it end up like this?

312
00:20:37,341 --> 00:20:40,552
<i>So they were dating after all.</i>

313
00:20:41,345 --> 00:20:42,387
Probably.

314
00:20:44,139 --> 00:20:45,223
Also,

315
00:20:45,307 --> 00:20:48,769
it doesn't seem they coordinated
their stories and turned themselves in.

316
00:20:48,852 --> 00:20:51,104
When I told her Murano
had turned himself in,

317
00:20:51,188 --> 00:20:53,815
Miyuki looked genuinely surprised.

318
00:20:54,316 --> 00:20:56,860
It didn't seem like she knew beforehand.

319
00:20:57,736 --> 00:21:01,365
Then Murano really was
protecting Yanagihara?

320
00:21:03,575 --> 00:21:05,786
That might be true.

321
00:21:13,085 --> 00:21:13,919
What's wrong?

322
00:21:18,548 --> 00:21:20,550
My family was poor too,

323
00:21:21,051 --> 00:21:23,804
and I went to university
thanks to a scholarship.

324
00:21:24,930 --> 00:21:27,432
I joined the MHLW

325
00:21:27,516 --> 00:21:31,686
because I wanted to help people
like myself move forward, but…

326
00:21:33,230 --> 00:21:34,606
In my current position,

327
00:21:35,399 --> 00:21:36,775
I can't do anything.

328
00:21:42,864 --> 00:21:44,574
Is that really true?

329
00:21:47,828 --> 00:21:49,371
Even in your current position,

330
00:21:50,038 --> 00:21:51,748
isn't there something you can do?

331
00:21:53,291 --> 00:21:56,294
That's what you worked so hard for
at the Ministry, isn't it?

332
00:22:06,721 --> 00:22:07,848
Also,

333
00:22:08,473 --> 00:22:10,142
there's something bothering me.

334
00:22:11,893 --> 00:22:14,938
When her arm was grabbed by the victim,

335
00:22:15,480 --> 00:22:17,482
he apparently called her "Mari."

336
00:22:18,275 --> 00:22:19,359
Mari?

337
00:22:25,991 --> 00:22:27,117
Mari…

338
00:22:27,742 --> 00:22:28,785
What?

339
00:22:30,453 --> 00:22:31,538
Mari…

340
00:22:35,041 --> 00:22:38,879
<i>To have to depend on someone</i>
<i>who gets your name wrong…</i>

341
00:22:40,505 --> 00:22:43,341
<i>She felt pathetic</i>
<i>for having to live like that.</i>

342
00:22:48,221 --> 00:22:49,723
<i>She said that before she knew it,</i>

343
00:22:50,223 --> 00:22:52,350
<i>she was strangling him.</i>

344
00:22:54,519 --> 00:22:57,189
Maybe she was just at her limit.

345
00:22:57,272 --> 00:22:59,983
The victim laid hands on many women.

346
00:23:00,066 --> 00:23:01,401
She might be one of them.

347
00:23:03,069 --> 00:23:05,739
It might have something
to do with the case.

348
00:23:05,822 --> 00:23:07,365
I'll look into it.

349
00:23:23,673 --> 00:23:24,799
Let's get married.

350
00:23:26,092 --> 00:23:27,219
It's impossible.

351
00:23:28,428 --> 00:23:29,512
We can't escape.

352
00:23:33,308 --> 00:23:35,310
If only he wasn't here,

353
00:23:37,562 --> 00:23:40,232
I could be with the person I love forever.

354
00:23:57,249 --> 00:24:00,377
<i>Even in your current position,</i>
<i>isn't there something you can do?</i>

355
00:24:02,212 --> 00:24:04,714
I had to do my best to get out of there…

356
00:24:13,390 --> 00:24:14,474
All right.

357
00:24:24,484 --> 00:24:25,318
What…

358
00:24:27,988 --> 00:24:29,572
You were working until morning?

359
00:24:30,198 --> 00:24:31,616
As you can see.

360
00:24:32,575 --> 00:24:35,412
So, did you find any poison?

361
00:24:35,495 --> 00:24:36,413
No.

362
00:24:37,163 --> 00:24:40,000
I've tried a thousand patterns,

363
00:24:40,542 --> 00:24:43,628
but the parameter settings
are still infinite.

364
00:24:49,050 --> 00:24:49,968
Yes?

365
00:24:50,051 --> 00:24:51,511
Ms. Dojima, it's an emergency!

366
00:24:51,594 --> 00:24:54,681
The ashtray believed to be
the murder weapon has been found!

367
00:24:56,516 --> 00:24:58,476
The shape of the discovered ashtray

368
00:24:58,560 --> 00:25:01,062
matches the wound on Kuriyama's head.

369
00:25:01,146 --> 00:25:03,273
Murano's fingerprints
were also detected on the ashtray.

370
00:25:04,024 --> 00:25:06,192
What about
Miyuki Yanagihara's fingerprints?

371
00:25:06,276 --> 00:25:07,569
None of hers.

372
00:25:08,069 --> 00:25:11,740
So the culprit really was
Murano after all?

373
00:25:11,823 --> 00:25:12,741
Yes.

374
00:25:12,824 --> 00:25:15,744
The prosecution has also decided
to indict Murano.

375
00:25:16,828 --> 00:25:18,163
Please wait.

376
00:25:18,246 --> 00:25:19,873
The cause of death was drowning.

377
00:25:19,956 --> 00:25:23,209
Murano's statement says
that he strangled him. It doesn't add up.

378
00:25:23,293 --> 00:25:24,753
We know that.

379
00:25:25,837 --> 00:25:28,840
But evidence backing the crime
has surfaced.

380
00:25:28,923 --> 00:25:32,010
According to the police,
it appears that Murano is the culprit.

381
00:25:32,510 --> 00:25:35,221
The investigation task force
is being disbanded.

382
00:26:01,581 --> 00:26:02,832
Wait!

383
00:26:39,869 --> 00:26:42,247
The mystery has not yet been solved.

384
00:26:43,915 --> 00:26:46,459
What poison did Miyuki administer,

385
00:26:47,419 --> 00:26:51,548
and why does Murano's statement
differ from the cause of death?

386
00:26:54,092 --> 00:26:55,844
I'm going to the scene again.

387
00:26:56,511 --> 00:27:00,181
There might be a piece
we haven't found yet.

388
00:27:06,020 --> 00:27:06,855
Okay!

389
00:27:12,569 --> 00:27:14,446
We're going to
Miyuki Yanagihara's apartment.

390
00:27:14,529 --> 00:27:15,655
What?

391
00:27:15,738 --> 00:27:18,992
We can't just let it end
like this either, can we?

392
00:27:20,785 --> 00:27:21,870
Yes, ma'am!

393
00:27:46,561 --> 00:27:47,645
Cute.

394
00:27:48,354 --> 00:27:50,356
Did it belong to the victim, you think?

395
00:28:05,371 --> 00:28:06,664
Hey, you!

396
00:28:07,749 --> 00:28:09,501
-Wait!
-Stop!

397
00:28:14,130 --> 00:28:15,840
Did you find something?

398
00:28:16,883 --> 00:28:19,969
No, nothing in particular.

399
00:28:22,972 --> 00:28:24,057
Doctor,

400
00:28:24,140 --> 00:28:26,351
that pen is bothering you, right?

401
00:28:26,434 --> 00:28:29,896
Compared to the victim's
other belongings, it's quite different.

402
00:28:29,979 --> 00:28:32,524
I wonder why. It's a mystery.

403
00:28:32,607 --> 00:28:34,025
Dr. Masumi,

404
00:28:34,108 --> 00:28:37,570
no toxins were detected
in the line test either.

405
00:28:38,154 --> 00:28:39,614
Okay.

406
00:28:39,697 --> 00:28:42,992
Let's go back to basics and start over
from the elemental analysis.

407
00:28:43,076 --> 00:28:44,202
Okay.

408
00:28:46,037 --> 00:28:46,996
It's Mari-chan!

409
00:28:48,206 --> 00:28:49,165
Mari-chan?

410
00:28:49,749 --> 00:28:50,917
<i>Magical Detective Mari.</i>

411
00:28:51,000 --> 00:28:52,752
It's a new popular anime.

412
00:28:52,836 --> 00:28:54,087
Oh, okay.

413
00:28:57,841 --> 00:29:00,593
Is this girl called "Mari"?

414
00:29:01,177 --> 00:29:01,970
Yes.

415
00:29:02,846 --> 00:29:03,930
Is something wrong?

416
00:29:04,013 --> 00:29:08,309
When the victim woke up,
he apparently called Miyuki "Mari."

417
00:29:08,393 --> 00:29:13,314
The police couldn't find any Mari
who knew the victim.

418
00:29:13,398 --> 00:29:17,026
But surely, it couldn't be
an anime character, right?

419
00:29:22,949 --> 00:29:24,951
I found out the name of the poison.

420
00:29:25,660 --> 00:29:26,828
What is it?

421
00:29:28,454 --> 00:29:29,414
Aconitine.

422
00:29:31,583 --> 00:29:33,501
Of course, we wouldn't find that.

423
00:29:33,585 --> 00:29:35,628
We don't usually test for that.

424
00:29:35,712 --> 00:29:37,547
I'll cross-reference it with the database.

425
00:29:37,630 --> 00:29:38,840
Wait.

426
00:29:40,049 --> 00:29:42,385
We did not find aconitine in the body.

427
00:29:44,512 --> 00:29:46,139
The pieces might be

428
00:29:46,973 --> 00:29:48,641
coming together.

429
00:29:56,858 --> 00:30:00,278
Regarding the poison
you said you gave to Kuriyama,

430
00:30:00,361 --> 00:30:04,115
no matter how much we investigated,
it could not be detected.

431
00:30:05,617 --> 00:30:07,952
However, that was only natural.

432
00:30:09,162 --> 00:30:12,832
Kuriyama had not ingested poison
in the first place.

433
00:30:14,083 --> 00:30:15,835
What do you mean?

434
00:30:17,211 --> 00:30:19,881
I put poison in his drink.

435
00:30:19,964 --> 00:30:24,886
I heard you were called
"Mari" by the victim.

436
00:30:25,845 --> 00:30:27,305
What about it?

437
00:30:27,388 --> 00:30:30,725
Do you know who Mari is?

438
00:30:33,269 --> 00:30:35,939
I don't know.
Just some other woman, right?

439
00:30:36,022 --> 00:30:38,566
I thought so too at first.

440
00:30:38,650 --> 00:30:41,069
But no matter how much we investigated,

441
00:30:41,152 --> 00:30:44,489
we could not find any woman named Mari.

442
00:30:45,114 --> 00:30:47,659
The only Mari found…

443
00:30:48,743 --> 00:30:49,953
was this girl.

444
00:30:51,120 --> 00:30:52,455
From an anime?

445
00:30:53,289 --> 00:30:55,208
Her name is Mari,

446
00:30:55,792 --> 00:30:57,210
from <i>Magical Detective Mari.</i>

447
00:30:58,378 --> 00:31:02,131
Kuriyama was a die-hard fan
of this character.

448
00:31:03,341 --> 00:31:07,553
You're saying I was mistaken
for an anime character?

449
00:31:07,637 --> 00:31:08,596
Yes.

450
00:31:09,347 --> 00:31:11,182
When we examined the hippocampus,

451
00:31:11,265 --> 00:31:13,476
the part of the brain
which governs memory,

452
00:31:13,559 --> 00:31:15,853
we saw necrosis in the surrounding area.

453
00:31:15,937 --> 00:31:17,021
In other words,

454
00:31:17,647 --> 00:31:20,024
Kuriyama suffered
a consciousness disorder,

455
00:31:20,108 --> 00:31:23,820
and as a result,
he mistook you for his beloved Mari.

456
00:31:25,279 --> 00:31:29,200
That's because of the poison, right?

457
00:31:29,283 --> 00:31:30,410
No.

458
00:31:30,493 --> 00:31:33,746
Because the poison you used

459
00:31:34,247 --> 00:31:35,915
was aconitine.

460
00:31:39,335 --> 00:31:43,965
The person who purchased
the poison for you told us.

461
00:31:44,549 --> 00:31:45,383
What?

462
00:31:47,093 --> 00:31:48,094
Of course,

463
00:31:48,678 --> 00:31:51,597
you know who that person is.

464
00:31:51,681 --> 00:31:56,185
You've been silent all this time
to protect him, haven't you?

465
00:32:00,606 --> 00:32:02,025
The one who bought the poison

466
00:32:02,817 --> 00:32:03,860
was the host…

467
00:32:06,863 --> 00:32:07,989
Kaito Miura.

468
00:32:08,072 --> 00:32:10,700
No! I bought it myself!

469
00:32:10,783 --> 00:32:13,786
Kaito Miura has already
admitted his involvement.

470
00:32:15,163 --> 00:32:18,332
I was worried there was evidence left
of me buying that poison,

471
00:32:18,416 --> 00:32:20,960
so I went and checked Miyuki's place.

472
00:32:21,044 --> 00:32:23,963
Does that mean you also had
a grudge against Kuriyama?

473
00:32:24,047 --> 00:32:27,258
He found out I was trying to
go independent and was interfering.

474
00:32:27,341 --> 00:32:30,803
But I only bought the poison,
Miyuki is the one who did it.

475
00:32:30,887 --> 00:32:34,015
I won't be charged with murder, right?

476
00:32:36,851 --> 00:32:38,519
It's not Kaito's fault.

477
00:32:40,396 --> 00:32:41,898
I just asked him.

478
00:32:41,981 --> 00:32:44,275
He has nothing to do with it!

479
00:32:44,358 --> 00:32:48,946
You put the aconitine purchased
by Mr. Miura into the protein.

480
00:32:49,030 --> 00:32:51,616
However, if aconitine is ingested,

481
00:32:51,699 --> 00:32:55,661
brain function is instantly destroyed,
so one would never regain consciousness.

482
00:32:55,745 --> 00:32:57,914
So, a disturbance of consciousness

483
00:32:57,997 --> 00:33:00,750
and mistaking you for Mari,
is not possible.

484
00:33:02,126 --> 00:33:03,795
That doesn't make sense.

485
00:33:04,378 --> 00:33:07,006
Then why did the owner collapse?

486
00:33:07,090 --> 00:33:11,969
That's because Kuriyama
had people trying to kill him twice.

487
00:33:13,054 --> 00:33:14,180
Twice?

488
00:33:14,764 --> 00:33:17,934
<i>That day, another person had visited</i>
<i>the owner's room</i>

489
00:33:18,518 --> 00:33:22,105
<i>between when you mixed the poison</i>
<i>into the drink</i>

490
00:33:22,688 --> 00:33:25,775
and you returning
to retrieve your earring.

491
00:33:33,116 --> 00:33:34,325
It was Murano.

492
00:33:36,536 --> 00:33:38,037
Murano?

493
00:33:38,121 --> 00:33:41,874
He said that he went
to ask the owner to release you.

494
00:33:43,000 --> 00:33:44,836
He confessed just now.

495
00:33:44,919 --> 00:33:47,088
Please let Miyuki go!

496
00:33:47,964 --> 00:33:49,757
Please, I beg you!

497
00:33:50,633 --> 00:33:52,260
Are you stupid?

498
00:34:14,615 --> 00:34:16,159
<i>But,</i>

499
00:34:16,242 --> 00:34:19,245
at that time, Kuriyama was not dead yet.

500
00:34:21,831 --> 00:34:25,042
He lost consciousness
because he was strangled,

501
00:34:25,126 --> 00:34:29,630
<i>and his breathing and pulse</i>
<i>became extremely weak.</i>

502
00:34:29,714 --> 00:34:32,175
<i>It's a so-called state of apparent death.</i>

503
00:34:33,551 --> 00:34:35,595
<i>Kuriyama regained consciousness</i>

504
00:34:35,678 --> 00:34:37,096
<i>exited the closet,</i>

505
00:34:37,180 --> 00:34:39,599
<i>and lost consciousness again.</i>

506
00:34:40,516 --> 00:34:43,519
<i>And then you came in.</i>

507
00:34:44,061 --> 00:34:45,521
<i>Seeing him like that,</i>

508
00:34:45,605 --> 00:34:49,692
<i>you mistakenly thought Kuriyama</i>
<i>had died from drinking the poison.</i>

509
00:34:49,775 --> 00:34:52,486
<i>However, Kuriyama,</i>
<i>who was still breathing,</i>

510
00:34:52,570 --> 00:34:54,822
<i>regained consciousness once more.</i>

511
00:34:54,906 --> 00:34:57,074
<i>And due to the consciousness disorder</i>

512
00:34:57,158 --> 00:34:59,827
<i>caused by the hypoxic state</i>
<i>from being strangled,</i>

513
00:34:59,911 --> 00:35:01,162
<i>he got your name…</i>

514
00:35:01,245 --> 00:35:02,330
Mari…

515
00:35:02,413 --> 00:35:03,831
<i>…wrong.</i>

516
00:35:03,915 --> 00:35:08,878
<i>That pushed you</i>
<i>to lay your hands on Kuriyama.</i>

517
00:35:10,171 --> 00:35:15,968
You and Murano both tried
to kill Kuriyama,

518
00:35:16,052 --> 00:35:18,930
and both of you failed.

519
00:35:19,597 --> 00:35:21,140
<i>However, in the end,</i>

520
00:35:22,058 --> 00:35:24,936
<i>you were the one who completed it.</i>

521
00:35:30,358 --> 00:35:31,817
Ms. Yanagihara,

522
00:35:32,401 --> 00:35:35,947
I am committing you to trial
on suspicion of murder.

523
00:35:41,577 --> 00:35:42,828
What about Murano?

524
00:35:43,704 --> 00:35:45,998
He will be charged with attempted murder.

525
00:35:47,875 --> 00:35:52,380
You hid the fact that you had entered
a relationship with Kaito Miura,

526
00:35:52,463 --> 00:35:56,884
and tried to get Murano
to kill the victim, didn't you?

527
00:35:56,968 --> 00:35:58,552
If only he wasn't here,

528
00:35:58,636 --> 00:36:01,639
I could be with the person I love forever.

529
00:36:03,140 --> 00:36:07,186
<i>But you got tired of Murano</i>
<i>never following through,</i>

530
00:36:07,895 --> 00:36:09,855
so you finally did it yourself.

531
00:36:11,023 --> 00:36:14,151
Yet coincidentally,
Murano followed through

532
00:36:14,944 --> 00:36:17,363
on the same day.

533
00:36:20,116 --> 00:36:22,243
I have a message from Murano.

534
00:36:23,077 --> 00:36:25,079
Please tell Miyuki this.

535
00:36:26,789 --> 00:36:28,291
This is my fault.

536
00:36:29,583 --> 00:36:31,419
I'm so sorry.

537
00:36:33,337 --> 00:36:34,171
But,

538
00:36:35,423 --> 00:36:38,467
let's both atone for our crimes

539
00:36:39,218 --> 00:36:40,303
and get married.

540
00:36:42,513 --> 00:36:44,724
I'll be waiting for her forever.

541
00:36:49,228 --> 00:36:51,355
You might have just been using him,

542
00:36:51,439 --> 00:36:53,566
but he was serious.

543
00:37:02,366 --> 00:37:04,285
Are you kidding me?

544
00:37:09,415 --> 00:37:11,500
Stupid useless man.

545
00:37:11,584 --> 00:37:14,045
Don't get ahead of yourself!

546
00:37:14,879 --> 00:37:21,010
It's because you failed to kill him
that I'm in this mess!

547
00:37:27,933 --> 00:37:28,768
And here…

548
00:37:35,649 --> 00:37:38,569
And here I thought
I could finally get out.

549
00:37:48,245 --> 00:37:49,538
Did you really…

550
00:37:52,416 --> 00:37:54,085
think that?

551
00:37:59,090 --> 00:38:00,549
You killed someone.

552
00:38:03,094 --> 00:38:05,721
Even if you managed to get out of this,

553
00:38:09,225 --> 00:38:10,684
by doing all this,

554
00:38:13,396 --> 00:38:14,980
did you really think

555
00:38:16,232 --> 00:38:17,900
you could move forward?

556
00:38:28,327 --> 00:38:29,412
Move forward?

557
00:38:32,998 --> 00:38:35,167
Why would you assume that?

558
00:38:37,169 --> 00:38:39,296
I never said anything about "forward."

559
00:38:41,424 --> 00:38:46,220
I just wanted to break away from the owner
and be with Kaito forever.

560
00:38:47,763 --> 00:38:49,598
I don't care about the future.

561
00:38:50,433 --> 00:38:53,144
As long as I'm happy now,
that's all that matters.

562
00:38:57,440 --> 00:38:59,024
Someone who's talented,

563
00:39:01,485 --> 00:39:03,696
has a good job,

564
00:39:05,865 --> 00:39:08,325
and lives without any hardship

565
00:39:10,619 --> 00:39:13,080
wouldn't understand my feelings.

566
00:39:17,626 --> 00:39:20,129
I even defaulted on my scholarship

567
00:39:21,088 --> 00:39:25,050
and used all the money I earned for Kaito.

568
00:39:31,807 --> 00:39:33,476
It was fun, though.

569
00:40:33,035 --> 00:40:34,161
I…

570
00:40:36,830 --> 00:40:38,958
didn't see anything.

571
00:40:49,677 --> 00:40:50,970
There are people

572
00:40:52,471 --> 00:40:54,723
in society waiting for help.

573
00:40:57,059 --> 00:41:01,272
I thought I was working for those people.

574
00:41:04,650 --> 00:41:06,360
But it was all just an ideal.

575
00:41:09,071 --> 00:41:11,865
I didn't see anything.

576
00:41:15,578 --> 00:41:18,789
Isn't it a good thing by itself
that you realized that?

577
00:41:30,301 --> 00:41:31,385
Hey.

578
00:41:32,052 --> 00:41:34,054
Your nose is running.

579
00:41:41,854 --> 00:41:43,022
Hey.

580
00:41:44,023 --> 00:41:45,232
You look ugly.

581
00:41:51,488 --> 00:41:53,324
Go on, cry.

582
00:42:08,839 --> 00:42:09,965
Ms. Kiryu.

583
00:42:10,049 --> 00:42:12,635
-Stamp this, please.
-Okay.

584
00:42:14,386 --> 00:42:17,598
Mark them all
as "by the end of today," please.

585
00:42:18,807 --> 00:42:19,975
-Okay.
-Okay.

586
00:42:23,687 --> 00:42:24,688
Wait.

587
00:42:25,481 --> 00:42:26,565
Dr. Honda…

588
00:42:29,985 --> 00:42:33,656
What does this LC-MS mean?

589
00:42:33,739 --> 00:42:34,865
What?

590
00:42:35,866 --> 00:42:39,036
Oh, it's the same as always,
so if you could just stamp it for now,

591
00:42:39,119 --> 00:42:39,995
No.

592
00:42:40,788 --> 00:42:42,039
As the supervisor,

593
00:42:42,122 --> 00:42:44,750
I want to really understand it
before I stamp it.

594
00:42:44,833 --> 00:42:45,876
Please tell me.

595
00:42:49,463 --> 00:42:50,839
Can't be helped…

596
00:42:51,423 --> 00:42:54,426
-I'm busy, you know?
-I'm sorry.

597
00:42:55,094 --> 00:42:56,845
Well, simply put,

598
00:42:56,929 --> 00:43:02,267
it means separating components
with LC and analyzing the mass.

599
00:43:03,727 --> 00:43:05,062
Analyzing mass?

600
00:43:05,145 --> 00:43:06,105
Yes.

601
00:43:06,188 --> 00:43:08,565
You mean like on a scale?

602
00:43:08,649 --> 00:43:09,692
No, like I said…

603
00:43:10,401 --> 00:43:11,402
More documents?

604
00:43:12,194 --> 00:43:13,237
For LC-MS,

605
00:43:13,320 --> 00:43:15,489
I recommend this book.

606
00:43:16,490 --> 00:43:17,533
Thank you very much.

607
00:43:20,035 --> 00:43:22,746
LC… Liquid Chromatography?

608
00:43:23,747 --> 00:43:25,207
So what is LC-MS?

609
00:43:25,290 --> 00:43:27,626
It's that instrument over there.

610
00:43:36,093 --> 00:43:39,263
A child suspected of being abused
was in an accident.

611
00:43:39,346 --> 00:43:40,514
<i>What kind of screaming?</i>

612
00:43:40,597 --> 00:43:41,432
Are you okay?

613
00:43:41,515 --> 00:43:44,017
In the middle of the night,
suddenly, like "wahh!"

614
00:44:48,332 --> 00:44:51,001
Subtitle translation by: Maslin F.

